"{\"uid\": \"29news.com-2024-06-05-charlottesville-albemarle-police-participate-special-olympic-torch-run\", \"text\": \"CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. (WVIR) - Charlottesville Police Department and Albemarle County Police Department are participating in this year's Special Olympic Torch Run.  Each year law enforcement torch run members carry the \\\"Flame of Hope\\\" throughout the commonwealth to raise funds and awareness for Special Olympics Virginia athletes.  The three-mile course stretches from Wegmans all the way to CPD headquarters on Market Street.  \\\"When people call the police, they are not having their best day,\\\" Albemarle County Police Officer David Sprouse said. \\\"This is a great time for us to come out here on a voluntary basis and one, help them and raise awareness for their cause, but also for us to give back as law enforcement officers.\\\"  Each police department is competing to see who can be the top fund-raisers in the state.  To donate to ACPD's team clickhere.To donate to CPD's team clickhere.  Do you have a story idea? Send us your news tiphere.  Copyright 2024 WVIR. All rights reserved.\"}"